# Go Patterns & Conventions

## Project Layout
- `cmd/server/` — FX wiring (`main.go`), Echo routes (`routes/router.go`)
- `cmd/migrations/sql/` — Atlas SQL migrations + `atlas.sum`
- `internal/` — private application code (see `go-layering.mdc`)
- `pkg/` — small shared libraries (e.g. `pkg/correlationid/`)
- `docs/` — swag-generated OpenAPI (`swagger.yaml`, `swagger.json`, `docs.go`)

## Layered Flow
```
Handler (DTO) → Service → Repository (Model)
```
- **Handlers** (`internal/handlers/`): bind/validate Echo request → call service → `BaseHandler.HandleError` / `SuccessResponse`
- **Services** (`internal/services/`): business rules; use `context.Context`, not `echo.Context`
- **Repositories** (`internal/repositories/`): GORM access; return `internal/models`
- **DTOs** (`internal/dtos/`): JSON shapes at handler edges only

## Error Handling
- Prefer **`internal/errors.AppError`** + `ErrorHandler` over scattered `echo.NewHTTPError`
- **Exception**: `TenantIdentityAdminHandler` uses `echo.NewHTTPError` — match when editing that file
- Wrap low-level errors: `fmt.Errorf("operation: %w", err)`
- Use `errors.Is()` / `errors.As()` for comparison
- Error codes live in `internal/constants/` — reuse existing codes before adding new ones

## HTTP route surfaces

Registered in `cmd/server/routes/router.go`:

| Namespace | Paths | Notes |
|-----------|-------|-------|
| **OIDC (root)** | `/.well-known/jwks.json`, `/.well-known/openid-configuration`, `/authorize`, `/token`, `/userinfo`, `/oidc/login`, `/oidc/federation/:provider/start\|callback` | Browser SSO via `iam_session` cookie; see [docs/features/SSO_SESSION.md](../../docs/features/SSO_SESSION.md) |
| **App API** | `/api/v1/*` — health, register/login/refresh, webauthn, mfa, `/internal/tenants/...` | swag `@BasePath`; JWT on protected routes |
| **Docs** | `/swagger/*` | Non-prod only, basic auth |

When adding routes: pick root vs `/api/v1`; update `internal/middlewares/csrf.go` Skipper if the path needs CSRF exemption.

## HTTP Handlers (Echo)
- Embed `BaseHandler` for shared response helpers
- Bind with `c.Bind(&req)`; validate with struct tags / `validator`
- Delegate logic to services; keep handlers thin
- Wire handlers with **`Provide*`** FX constructors (e.g. `ProvideAuthHandler`)
- Add **swag annotations** on `/api/v1` handler methods when routes change

## Logging (global Zap)
- `logger.Init(level, env)` in `main` before FX starts — exposes `logger.Log` and `logger.Sugar`
- Use `logger.Sugar` / structured `logger.Log` in middleware and startup; **do not** introduce global `slog` or per-handler loggers unless refactoring the whole stack
- Request fields logged via `internal/middlewares/logging.go`; correlation ID via `internal/request/context.go` + `pkg/correlationid/`

## Dependency Injection (Uber FX)
- Wire constructors in `cmd/server/main.go` via `fx.Provide` / `fx.Invoke`
- Register routes in `cmd/server/routes/router.go` — no business logic there
- Pass interfaces to handlers/services for testability

## Context
- `ctx context.Context` first on service/repo functions that do I/O
- Never store context in structs
- Propagate context through the call chain; use timeouts for outbound calls

## Concurrency
- Use `context.Context` for cancellation
- Prefer `errgroup` for parallel tasks with error propagation
- Every goroutine must have an exit path

## Testing
- Colocate: `foo.go` → `foo_test.go` in the same package
- Table-driven tests with `t.Run(tt.name, ...)`
- Handlers: `httptest` + `echo.New()` + stub services/repos
- Integration tests: `//go:build integration` tag (see `go-testing.mdc`)
- Run: `make tests` (full), or scoped `make test-handlers`, `make test-services`, etc.

## Naming
- MixedCaps / mixedCaps; acronyms all caps: `HTTPStatus`, `OIDCHandler`, `UserID`
- Constructor: `NewXxx(...deps) *Xxx` or `ProvideXxx` for FX providers
